rComments: He's a great guy. Love him so freakin much. The best prof in UTSC cuz he cares about you. He's a tough grader for sure. remember his birthday is 12.17 and his time is your time! call him! good luck guys since this is a mandatory course for coop mgt& coop mib
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader']

rComments: Best prof ever! This course does teach you a lot of things. Heavy reading is needed, the midterm covers a lot of readings. Its hard to have a high score for this course, but you wont regret taking this course. The prof cares about his students and selling to offer advice. TAKE MGTA36!!!

rComments: He's the best professor I have encountered.

The most valuable class at UTSC ever, it wouldnt have been as good without Proffesor Howard and his TA teaching it. The things you will learn in this class, will help you do great things in school or any where else. The last class truely hit me how time flies so quickly. Credits to my great class mates, till next time Howard!
The course is intimidating as hell. If you can get through it, which you will cause he's not a hard marker, there's nothing that will phase you again LOL
He is awesome
Most fun class in my first semester at UTSC, would take it again

The course is VERY useful but difficult at the same time. The exam is in the first 2 weeks so study ASAP. After the exam and 2 Impromptus, marks start to rise. The course really helps bring out confidence for 1st-year students and will improve presentation skills by 100%. It is really hard to get an A. I'm a decent speaker and ended with a high 70

Howard is a FANTASTIC prof. I always believed that I was shy and terrible at presentations. The beginning of the course was NOT easy - you have to do a couple of impromptus, which will be the scariest thing ever. Honestly though, Howard will really put you out there, but TRUST ME, don't drop. It's fun and as long as you improve, you'll do fine.
Love him, love this class. Hard grader, but gives useful feedbacks. Probably the most inspiring course I've taken so far. Really helped me with public speaking, tho I didn't get a high grade.
Unless you've been screaming your head off and emphasizing every other word, regardless of improvement you'll end up with a B. Work hard on the midterm; makes a huge difference.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Gives good feedback', 'Tough grader']

rComments: Very inconsistent marking scheme. In the first week I loved this course until about halfway through. Put so much effort in to try and improve my speaking skills even though I was already a good speaker but results never came. The clarity of what I needed to do to improve was poor. If you think you deserved an A you'll probably get a B.

THE MOST LIFE CHANGING CLASS YOU WILL EVER BE IN. Your grade, no matter how good or bad, will never match how much you learn and grow. I was not a shy person, but this class pushed me out of my comfort zone! I WOULD TAKE IT AGAIN IF I COULD. I love him, he was so helpful and kind. You could call him at 3am and he would answer. Hes an amazing person
Best Class Ever.

rComments: First few classes were very intimidating and your mark will definitely be low. After the midterm, however, you will find that your presentation skills will improve greatly as well as your marks. Started with a D and ended with an A.

Love this course. I wanted an A but in the beginning Howard said it's not gonna be that kind of course, so I didn't take it too seriously. But through out the course it has proven itself to be useful and informative. Definitely work hard on the presentations, midterm is all memorization. Howard actually wants to help you, so let him :)
Great prof!!! Want him again for other courses.
great prof!!!

Be prepared to commit a lot of your time and put in a lot of effort. This course will not get you an A easily, but you'll become a confident speaker after having taken this course. This course is more about developing lifetime skills, coming out of your comfort zone and making some friends. You will both hate and miss it a lot.

Great Prof!!! Best class ever in my university career, Is not easy course, I hate going class, but I have to. But at the end of the day, he will make you proud of you. Beyond grades, it's guaranteed that you will gain lot of friends, you will miss your class and your friends and even him right after the last class!
No textbook needed for this class. A great proff. Have to put A LOT of effort into this course and time. You will learn a lot! By the end of this course, you can do presentations in your sleep!

I feel that this course is more of a drama class then a management course, though good communication skills can be learned. Prof can be inconsistent sometimes and the course requires a great deal of your time.
He won't the Prof of the Year AWARD!
he demands A LOT..its a course that takes a lot of time from your schedule.he doesnt give As but u learn alot in his class. EXPECT to work your butt off and get a B..
best prof to teach this class. very useful class for improving communication skills

the course could be useful if it was delivered differently. howard is inconsistent with his marking and doesn't give much direction. he's a nice guy but the course just isnt worth the money. it's too subjective
ok..this was NOT an easy course. prof was really nice...but inconsistant with what he wanted. that is one of the most annoying thing. but a great course to improve some life long skills.
